"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The code incorrectly uses the `np.insert` function. The `np.insert` function is being called with the first argument as a 1D slice of the 2D array `arr`, which is correct. However, the second argument (the index where the value should be inserted) is set to 1, which is valid. The issue arises because the `np.insert` function does not modify the original array in place; it returns a new array. Therefore, the assignment `arr[i] = np.insert(arr[i], 1, 3)` will lead to a shape mismatch when trying to assign a 5-element array back to a 4-element slice of `arr`. This will raise a ValueError.\",\n  \"patch\": \"6c6\\n<     arr[i] = np.insert(arr[i], 1, 3)\\n---\\n>     arr[i] = np.insert(arr[i], 1, 3).reshape(-1)\"\n}"